;{{nihongo|The Duke of Normandy|ノルマンディー公|Norumandī Kō}}
:{{voiced by|Takaya Hashi<ref name="More-Cast-and-Premiere"/>|[[Jay Hickman (actor)|Jay Hickman]]<ref name="DubCast"/>}}
:The Home Secretary of the Albion Kingdom and Princess Charlotte's uncle. He handles the Kingdom's espionage affairs and personally has hunted down potential defectors from the Kingdom, either to use them for counter-espionage against the Commonwealth's agents or kill them outright.
;{{nihongo|Gazelle|ガゼル|Gazeru}}
:{{voiced by|Yūko Iida<ref name="More-Cast-and-Premiere"/>|Melanie Burke<ref name="DubCast"/>}}
:One of the Duke of Normandy's most-trusted agents, a dark-skinned woman who collects information and can kill anyone who poses a threat to her employer.

==Media==
===Anime===
The anime series is animated by [[3Hz|Studio 3Hz]] and [[Actas]].<ref name="studio and game"/> The series is directed by Masaki Tachibana, with scripts written by [[Ichirō Ōkouchi]] and character designs by [[Kouhaku Kuroboshi]] and Yukie Akiya. The series aired from July 9<ref name="More-Cast-and-Premiere">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-08/princess-principal-tv-anime-video-reveals-more-cast-july-9-debut/.117231|title=Princess Principal TV Anime's Video Reveals More Cast, July 9 Debut|website=Anime News Network|date=June 9, 2017|accessdate=June 9, 2017}}</ref> to September 24, 2017. The opening theme song is "The Other Side of the Wall" performed by Void_Chords and MARU, and the ending theme is "A Page of My Story" performed by [[Ayaka Imamura]], Akira Sekine, [[Yō Taichi]], [[Akari Kageyama]], and [[Nozomi Furuki]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-10/princess-principal-tv-anime-reveals-theme-song-artists/.115903|title=Princess Principal TV Anime Reveals Theme Song Artists|website=Anime News Network|date=May 10, 2017|accessdate=May 10, 2017}}</ref><ref name="Song"/> [[Sentai Filmworks]] has licensed the anime and streamed it on [[Amazon Prime Video]] in the U.S. and other streaming sites elsewhere.<ref name="Song">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-27/sentai-filmworks-licenses-princess-principal-for-summer-simulcast/.118077|title=Sentai Filmworks Licenses Princess Principal for Summer Simulcast|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=June 27, 2017|date=June 27, 2017}}</ref> [[MVM Films]] has licensed the series in the UK.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=MVMEntertainment|author=@MVM_UK|number=924262725697622016|date=October 28, 2017|title=Latest batch of announcements. Coming next year we've got Land of the Lustrous, Love & Lies, Made in Abyss and Princess Principal.}}</ref>

