===Films===
A six-series anime film adaptation of the series which will premiere in 2019 was announced on April 29, 2018. The series will follow on from the events of the last episode of the series.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Loo|first1=Egan|title=Princess Principal Anime Gets 6 Sequel Films Starting in 2019|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-04-29/princess-principal-anime-gets-6-sequel-films-starting-in-2019/.130989|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=April 29, 2018|date=April 29, 2018}}</ref>

==Reception==
''Princess Principal'' has garnered significant praise from critics, with many calling it one of the best anime of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.inquisitr.com/4636064/princess-principal-season-2-director-masaki-tachibana-movie-pripri-sequel-anime-nyc-2017-ange-figure/|title=''Princess Principal'' Season 2: Director Masaki Tachibana Talks Movie, ‘PriPri’ Sequel Hopes At Anime NYC 2017|first=Patrick|last=Frye|publisher=[[Inquisitr]]|date=November 20, 2017|accessdate=May 2, 2018}}</ref><ref name="kotaku">{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/our-top-four-summer-2017-anime-picks-1797280129|title=Our Top Four Summer 2017 Anime Picks|first=Cecilia|last=D'Anastasio|publisher=[[Kotaku]]|date=July 26, 2017|accessdate=May 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2017-09-27/the-best-and-worst-anime-of-summer-2017/.121908|title=The Best and Worst Anime of Summer 2017|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 27, 2017|accessdate=May 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2017-12-30/the-best-anime-of-2017/christopher-farris-and-paul-jensen/.125906|title=Christopher Farris and Paul Jensen|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 30, 2017|accessdate=May 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2017-12-27/the-best-anime-of-2017/theron-martin-rebecca-silverman-and-zac-bertschy/.125695|title=Theron Martin, Rebecca Silverman & Zac Bertschy|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 27, 2017|accessdate=May 2, 2018}}</ref> ''[[Kotaku]]'' picked it as one of best summer 2017 anime series, with writer Cecilia D'Anastasio noting that the "soundtrack is jazzy madness. Its animation is pure beauty. It’s full of sharp writing, surprises and edge-of-your-seat intrigue."<ref name="kotaku"/>

The music gained positive comments, especially the opening theme song to the series, "The Other Side of the Wall". The song was named by Chris Farris and Theron Martin from Anime News Network as the best theme song of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2017-12-28/the-best-anime-of-2017/the-best-theme-songs-of-2017/.125845|title=The Best Theme Songs of 2017|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 28, 2017|accessdate=May 2, 2018}}</ref> It was also nominated for the best opening song at the 2017 [[Crunchyroll]]'s Anime Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2018/03/01/revealing-the-judges-picks-for-the-anime-awards|title=Revealing the Judge's Picks for the Anime Awards|publisher=[[Crunchyroll]]|first=Cayla|last=Coats|date=March 2, 2018|accessdate=May 2, 2018}}</ref>

